parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wiring harness can cause electrical shorts, engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or even death.
symptoms: smoke or fire in the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disintegration of the engine wiring harness can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine wiring harness insulation breaks into brittle pieces
causing the vehicle to shut off or stall
often without warning indicators on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leaks and Gasket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks and gasket failure can cause damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Excessive oil leaks on both sides of the engine
oil leak into the cooling system
and engine stalling or shutting off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Mass air meter failure can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: often recurring after replacement of the mass air meter.
